On Windows, I express myself through <a href="http://aptana.com/">Aptana</a> (Aptana is <em>better</em> than Dreamweaver. Take this as in the objective tone; and it's free. So, <strong>stop </strong>using Dreamweaver. I mean it.). On OS X, through <a href="http://www.panic.com/coda/">Coda</a>. I may consider <a href="http://macromates.com/">TextMate </a>once I determine a time-inexpensive and unobtrusive FTP workflow.

Buh'really I want to remind myself of this <a href="http://code.google.com/p/zen-coding/">Zen Coding</a> business. Not that I could forget. I installed it immediately (others covered, beyond Coda, Aptana and TextMate, include WebIDE, TopStyle, NetBeans, Espresso (!), Sublime Text). It's mind-blowingly <em>ow</em>esome.

